# CODEOWNERS — automatic reviewer assignment for sensitive paths.
#
# GitHub requests review from the listed owner(s) when a PR changes any
# matching path. Combined with a "Require review from Code Owners" branch
# protection rule on `main`, this becomes a hard gate: no enforcement-
# sensitive merge without explicit maintainer approval.
#
# Syntax: <path-glob> <@owner> [<@owner> ...]
# First-match wins — order matters, most-specific last.

# Default: maintainer reviews anything not covered below.
